Description: Fragment of pottery amphora rim; Fikellura ware; cream slip on inside and outside; vertical brown-red strokes on outside of rim above horizontal band, brown-red glaze on lower part of rim and on neck; broad brown-red band on top and top of inside of rim. Hard, orange clay, between Munsell 2.5YR 6/4 (light reddish brown) and Munsell 5YR 6/6 (light red); little mica.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 340)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
